##  Overview

Virtual Mouse is a computer vision project that uses your webcam to detect hand landmarks in real time and maps your finger movements to mouse actions. It eliminates the need for a physical mouse by interpreting specific hand gestures as mouse events — move, click, scroll, and drag.

This project uses **MediaPipe Hands** for accurate 21-point hand landmark detection and **PyAutoGUI** to control the system mouse programmatically.

---

## ⚙️ How It Works

```
Webcam Frame
     ↓
MediaPipe Hand Landmark Detection (21 points)
     ↓
Finger State Analysis (up/down per finger)
     ↓
Gesture Classification
     ↓
PyAutoGUI Mouse Event (move / click / scroll / drag)
```

1. **Webcam capture** — OpenCV reads frames from your webcam in real time
2. **Hand detection** — MediaPipe Hands detects and tracks 21 hand landmarks per frame
3. **Finger state detection** — The system checks which fingers are raised or folded using landmark Y-coordinates
4. **Gesture classification** — Finger combinations are mapped to specific mouse gestures
5. **Mouse control** — PyAutoGUI translates the index fingertip position to screen coordinates and triggers mouse events

---

##  Gesture Controls

| Fingers Up | Gesture | Mouse Action |
|---|---|---|
| Index only | Point | Move cursor |
| Index + Middle | Peace / Neutral | Freeze cursor |
| Thumb + Index close | Pinch | Left click |
| Thumb + Middle close | Pinch alt | Right click |
| Index + Middle (scroll zone) | Scroll | Scroll up/down |
| All fingers down | Fist | Click and drag |
| All fingers up | Open palm | Stop / idle |

> Gesture mappings can be customized in `config.py`.

